To create a searchable Bootstrap dropdown with options generated from a MySQL query, you'll need to follow these steps:

1. **Set Up Your Backend**: Write a PHP script to fetch data from the MySQL database.
2. **Set Up Your Frontend**: Use Bootstrap to create the dropdown and handle the search functionality.

### Step 1: Set Up Your Backend

Create a PHP script to fetch data from the MySQL database and return it in a JSON format. For example, let's assume you have a table named `actors` with columns `id`, `first_name`, and `last_name`.

** actors.php (Backend)**
```php
<?php
header('Content-Type: application/json');

// Database configuration
$host = 'localhost';
$dbname = 'your_database_name';
$username = 'your_username';
$password = 'your_password';

try {
    $pdo = new PDO("mysql:host=$host;dbname=$dbname", $username, $password);
    $pdo->setAttribute(PDO::ATTR_ERRMODE, PDO::ERRMODE_EXCEPTION);

    // Prepare the SQL query
    $stmt = $pdo->prepare("SELECT id, first_name, last_name FROM actors WHERE first_name LIKE ? OR last_name LIKE ?");
    $searchTerm = '%' . $_GET['term'] . '%'; // Search term from AJAX request
    $stmt->execute([$searchTerm, $searchTerm]);

    // Fetch results
    $results = $stmt->fetchAll(PDO::FETCH_ASSOC);

    // Return JSON response
    echo json_encode($results);

} catch (PDOException $e) {
    echo json_encode(['error' => $e->getMessage()]);
}
?>
```

### Step 2: Set Up Your Frontend

Use Bootstrap to create the dropdown and handle the search functionality using AJAX.

**HTML and JavaScript (Frontend)**
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Searchable Dropdown</title>
    <!-- Bootstrap CSS -->
    <link href="https://stackpath.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.5.2/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
</head>
<body>

<div class="container mt-5">
    <div class="input-group">
        <input type="text" class="form-control" id="searchInput" placeholder="Search by name...">
        <div class="input-group-append">
            <button class="btn btn-primary" type="button" id="searchButton">Search</button>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="dropdown mt-3" id="actorDropdown">
        <button class="btn btn-secondary dropdown-toggle" type="button" id="dropdownMenuButton" data-toggle="dropdown" aria-haspopup="true" aria-expanded="false">
            Select Actor
        </button>
        <div class="dropdown-menu" aria-labelledby="dropdownMenuButton">
            <!-- Dropdown items will be populated here -->
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<!-- Bootstrap JS and jQuery -->
<script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.5.1.slim.min.js"></script>
<script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@popperjs/core@2.9.2/dist/umd/popper.min.js"></script>
<script src="https://stackpath.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.5.2/js/bootstrap.min.js"></script>

<script>
$(document).ready(function () {
    // Function to fetch and populate the dropdown
    function fetchActors() {
        $.ajax({
            url: "actors.php",
            method: "GET",
            data: { term: $("#searchInput").val() },
            success: function (response) {
                var dropdown = $('#actorDropdown .dropdown-menu');
                dropdown.empty(); // Clear existing options

                if (response.error) {
                    dropdown.append('<li class="dropdown-item">No results found.</li>');
                } else {
                    response.forEach(function (actor) {
                        dropdown.append(`<a class="dropdown-item" href="#">${actor.first_name} ${actor.last_name}</a>`);
                    });
                }
            },
            error: function (xhr, status, error) {
                console.log("Error: " + xhr.responseText);
            }
        });
    }

    // Handle search button click
    $("#searchButton").click(function () {
        fetchActors();
    });

    // Handle input change
    $("#searchInput").on('input', function () {
        fetchActors();
    });
});
</script>

</body>
</html>
```

### Explanation

1. **Backend (`actors.php`)**:
   - Connects to the MySQL database.
   - Uses a prepared statement to safely query the database based on the search term.
   - Returns the results in JSON format.

2. **Frontend**:
   - Uses Bootstrap for styling.
   - Uses jQuery to handle the search functionality.
   - When the search input changes or the search button is clicked, it sends an AJAX request to the backend to fetch the relevant actors.
   - The response is used to dynamically update the dropdown menu with the actor names.

This setup allows you to create a searchable dropdown that fetches data from a MySQL database and updates dynamically based on user input.

